reviews.reviewText: Review:I recently purchased the Magnetic case for my iPhone 14 Plus, and I must say I am thoroughly impressed. This case offers the perfect combination of style, functionality, and durability.First and foremost, the design of the case is fantastic. The slim profile and sleek finish complement the iPhone 14 Plus beautifully. It maintains the phone's original aesthetics while providing complete protection. The magnetic functionality adds a touch of convenience, allowing for easy attachment to magnetic mounts or accessories.In terms of functionality, this case delivers. The precise cutouts ensure easy access to all buttons, ports, and speakers. The tactile buttons offer a satisfying click response. The raised edges around the screen and camera provide added protection against scratches and drops, giving me peace of mind.Furthermore, the durability of this case is worth mentioning. The high-quality materials used in its construction ensure long-lasting protection. The case has a solid feel to it and withstands everyday wear and tear effortlessly. I have dropped my phone on a few occasions, and the case has proven its ability to absorb impact and protect my precious device.Another standout feature is the excellent grip provided by the. It feels secure in my hand, reducing the chances of accidental slips and drops. This is especially important for such a large phone like the iPhone 14 Plus.Lastly, I appreciate the attention to detail in the packaging. The case arrived in a neat and protective box, ensuring it reached me in pristine condition.Overall, I highly recommend the Magnetic case for the iPhone 14 Plus. It provides stylish, reliable, and comprehensive protection for your device. Whether you're looking for a case that offers convenience, functionality, or simply a sleek design, this case checks all the boxes. Don't hesitate to invest in this fantastic accessory for your iPhone 14 Plus.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for make it yourself case
reviews.reviewText: This has been a great case for my iPhone 15 Pro Max. Reason being is I smoke cigars, and wanted something I could put my favorite cigar labels in and now when people see my case, they ask where I got a case like this. It is very durable and would like to say that it does the job well. Only thing I needed to do was remove the plastic screen cover, and remove the waterproof casing to get good sound out of the speakers. Otherwise it was really muffled. You do not need water protection with this phone as it can go under water up to 250ft for 30 minutes without a case, so really the need to protect from water really isn't needed. The screen protector either. just get a glass screen protector to go over it, and you got yourself a really good case.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A must have set for your phone!
reviews.reviewText: I was apprehensive about what this case might be like but needed a quick fix for a new phone. Turns out, the case is decent, enough. It’s easy to hold onto the phone, and isn’t slippery like many. Feel like it’s got enough protection if it falls to protect it. Nice!The accessories with cases are usually junk. In this case though, they are decent too. Screen protector is glass and went on easily, and the camera protector the same thing. I’m glad they include two of each because I broke the one screen protector being careless getting it out of the case it comes nested in. That’s my bad. And I used one of the camera protectors by removing it when it looked like something was under it, but it turns out the lower camera has some weird optical illusion when you look at it.So just buy this kit and save yourself some cash. It’s complete and all you need. Feels protected!

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Water resistant but can cause glare on camera lense
reviews.reviewText: So far I really like this case. It works well. Protects my phone and keeps it dry. Sometimes I notice a glare and reflection in my photos bc of the lens protectors — especially in low light. This is a little upsetting to me considering I use my phone for spontaneous photos in my line of work. The case is a bit bulky for your pocket, but it’s actually relatively slim considering how protective it is. Make sure to expose your mic when recording/talking on the phone bc it definitely muffles it and makes audio sound “crunchy.”
